"Smartphone Gadget Makes Old Cars Smart",
http://spectrum.ieee.org/cars-that-think/transportation/advanced-cars/smartphone-gadget-makes-old-cars-smart
In this article one reads one of the central issues of this research: how to make driving smarter. It tells us also some
of the many possibilities of the OBD 2 connector when associated with an smartphone such as upgrading an old car into a 
smart one. This has many advantages, according to the article, from helping share the gas account to sanding SOS messages when a crash is dettected
